Bank Churn Prediction Project¶

Objective:

Given a Bank customer, build a neural network-based classifier that can determine whether they will leave or not.

1 - Prepare the dataset¶

2 - Deep Neural Network Model¶

Initialize & build the model. Identify the points of improvement and implement the same. Note that you need to demonstrate at least two models(the original and the improved one) and highlight the differences to complete this point. You can also demonstrate more models.

In [80]:
# Initialize the constructor
model = Sequential()
In [81]:
#Adding layers (layers and activation)
model.add(Dense(64, input_shape = (13,), activation = 'elu'))
model.add(Dense(32, activation = 'relu'))
model.add(Dense(1, activation = 'sigmoid'))
In [98]:
#Compile model 
optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.01)
model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer=optimizer , metrics = ['accuracy'])

By increasing the number of epochs, we cna see the model converging for the trained data and getting much better (0.8911). However, after ~60 epoches, the accrurae of the validation set decreases. This indicates that the model acccuracy increases to the detriment of the overfitting.

# Let's try a third model - this time, we increase the percentage of data for validation.

# Initialize the constructor
model3 = Sequential()
#Adding layers (layers and activation) 
model3.add(Dense(64, input_shape = (13,), activation = 'elu'))
model3.add(Dense(32, activation = 'elu'))
model3.add(Dense(1, activation = 'elu'))
#Compile model
optimizer3 = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(0.01)
model3.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer=optimizer3 , metrics = ['accuracy'])
history3 = model3.fit(X_train, Y_train.values, validation_split=0.3, batch_size = 100, epochs = 500, verbose = 1)

## function to get confusion matrix 
def draw_cm( actual, predicted ):
    cm = confusion_matrix( actual, predicted)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True,  fmt='.2f', xticklabels = [0,1] , yticklabels = [0,1] )
    plt.ylabel('Observed')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.show()
